#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:15
msgid ""
"GBIF processes taxonomic identifiers that are provided on the DwC elements "
"_scientificNameID_, _taxonID_ and _taxonConceptID_, when these identifiers "
"belong to any of the identifier schemes available. The identifiers are "
"retrieved from ChecklistBank and linked to taxa in the checklist. Currently, "
"the schemes available are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:48
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"|Identifier scheme |Description |REGEX Format |Example\n"
"\n"
"|https://artfakta.se/metadata/dyntaxa[Dyntaxa]\n"
"|A taxonomic database of the names of Swedish organisms, which contains information on current classification, recommended names and commonly used synonyms and misused names. \n"
"|^(?:dyntaxa\\|artfakta\\|urn:lsid:dyntaxa.se:Taxon):(\\\\d+)\n"
"|urn:lsid:dyntaxa.se:Taxon:106661\n"
"\n"
"|https://www.ipni.org/[IPNI]\n"
"|The International Plant Names Index (IPNI) is a nomenclatural index of names of vascular plants published under the Code of Nomenclature for algae fungi and plants (ICN).\n"
"|^(?:ipni\\|urn:lsid:ipni.org:names):(\\\\d+-[1-3])\n"
"|urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:50959-2\n"
"\n"
"|https://www.itis.gov/[ITIS]\n"
"|The Integrated Taxonomic Information System, an authoritative taxonomic information on plants, animals, fungi, and microbes of North America and the world.\n"
"|^(?:itis\\|tsn:)(\\\\d+)\n"
"|tsn:80028\n"
"\n"
"|https://www.nhm.ac.uk/our-science/data/uk-species/index[UK Species Inventory]\n"
"|A database of all UK wildlife, which provides the taxonomic foundation for most biological recording and analysis systems for the UK.\n"
"|^(?:uksi\\|nhm):((?:NHMSYS\\|NBNSYS)\\\\d{10})\n"
"|nhm:NBNSYS0000161229\n"
"\n"
"|https://www.marinespecies.org/index.php[WoRMS]\n"
"|The World Register of Marine Species (WoRMS) aims to provide an authoritative and comprehensive list of names of marine organisms, including information on synonymy.\n"
"|^(?:marinespecies\\|worms\\|aphia\\|urn:lsid:marinespecies.org:taxname):(\\\\d+)\n"
"|urn:lsid:marinespecies.org:taxname:538339\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "list example"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:53
msgid ""
"https://artfakta.se/metadata/dyntaxa[Dyntaxa]: A taxonomic database of the "
"names of Swedish organisms, which contains information on current "
"classification, recommended names and commonly used synonyms and misused "
"names. It should follow the format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:55
msgid "`+^(?:dyntaxa|artfakta|urn:lsid:dyntaxa.se:Taxon):(\\\\d+)`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:57
msgid "Example: urn:lsid:dyntaxa.se:Taxon:106661"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:58
msgid ""
"https://www.ipni.org/[IPNI]: The International Plant Names Index (IPNI) is a "
"nomenclatural index of names of vascular plants published under the Code of "
"Nomenclature for algae, fungi and plants (ICN).  It should follow the format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:60
msgid "`+^(?:ipni|urn:lsid:ipni.org:names):(\\\\d+-[1-3])`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:62
msgid "Example: urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:50959-2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:63
msgid ""
"https://www.itis.gov/[ITIS]: The Integrated Taxonomic Information System, an "
"authoritative taxonomic information on plants, animals, fungi, and microbes "
"of North America and the world. It should follow the format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:65
msgid "`+^(?:itis|tsn:)(\\\\d+)`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:67
msgid "Example: tsn:80028"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:68
msgid ""
"https://www.nhm.ac.uk/our-science/data/uk-species/index[UK Species "
"Inventory]: A database of all UK wildlife, which provides the taxonomic "
"foundation for most biological recording and analysis systems for the UK. It "
"should follow the format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:70
msgid "`+^(?:uksi|nhm):((?:NHMSYS|NBNSYS)\\\\d{10})`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:72
msgid "Example: nhm:NBNSYS0000161229"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:73
msgid ""
"https://www.marinespecies.org/index.php[WoRMS]: The World Register of Marine "
"Species (WoRMS) aims to provide an authoritative and comprehensive list of "
"names of marine organisms, including information on synonymy. It should "
"follow the format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:75
msgid ""
"`+^(?:marinespecies|worms|aphia|urn:lsid:marinespecies.org:taxname):(\\\\d+)`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:77
msgid "Example: urn:lsid:marinespecies.org:taxname:538339"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:80
msgid ""
"When both an identifier field and a _scientificName_ are provided, the "
"identifiers will be used first for matching, and if there is more than one "
"identifier present, the information on _taxonID_ will take precedence. A "
"match will also be made using the _scientificName_, and a comparison will be "
"made between the two matches."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSID-lookup.adoc:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://techdocs.gbif.org/en/data-use/occurrence-issues-and-flags#taxonomic-issues[Taxonomic flags and issues] are assigned during https://techdocs.gbif.org/en/data-processing/taxonomy-interpretation#taxonomic-indexes[pipeline processing] if inconsistencies are detected in the applied identifiers.   \n"
msgstr ""
